nson remains strong among academic and non-academic audiences alike. This is in part because her principal concerns – working-class representation, the status of women, capitalist crisis, war, anti-fascism – remain central to contentious politics today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aAnti-fascism.  aLabour.  aMarxism.  abiography.  afeminism.  asocialism.1 aPerry, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978071909849940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780719098499423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780719098499/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles